<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>There is a small problem with the _quote() function in the DB2 adapter when sing the version of the ibm_db2 driver which does recognize the db2_escape_string() function.  While the $value is escaped, it is not quoted, so the same value gets returned unchanged.  To fix it, you just need to add the " ' " character, similar to what is done in the parent class.  I copied the change here, plus I am attaching the changed file.</p>

<p>if (function_exists('db2_escape_string')) {
   return "'" . db2_escape_string($value) . "'";
}
return parent::_quote($value);</p>

